  "remarks": "Operational commander of Al-Qaida in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP)\n(QDe.129). Has been involved in raising funds and stockpiling arms for AQAP operations\nand activities in Yemen. Known associate of Qasim Yahya Mahdi al-Rimi (QDi.282) and Fahd\nMohammed Ahmed al-Quso (deceased). Father’s name is Ahmed Othman Al Omirah.\nReview pursuant to Security Council resolution 2368 (2017) was concluded on 24 November 2020. INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
